<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
A slender fragile plant easily fracturing when dry. The leaves are usually with three oblong-elliptic leaflets, much broader than in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="graniticola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea graniticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The sepals are quite variable and the tooth-like appendage is often reduced to little more than a swelling.
</paragraph>
